  <section id="cookie-policy" class="cookie-policy section">

    <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
      <div class="tos-header text-center" data-aos="fade-up">
        <span class="last-updated">Last updated: February 15, 2026</span>
        <h2>How we use cookies at RumboMed</h2>
        <p>We use our own and third-party cookies to improve your browsing experience, remember your preferences, and analyze our website traffic.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tos-content" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
        
        <div class="content-section mb-5">
          <h3>1. What is a cookie?</h3>
          <p>A cookie is a small text file that is stored in your browser when you visit almost any website. Its purpose is to enable the website to remember your visit when you return to that page, such as your language preferences, currency, or security settings, ensuring a smoother experience.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section mb-5">
          <h3>2. Types of cookies used</h3>
          <p>At RumboMed, we categorize the cookies we use into the following groups:</p>
          <ul class="list-items">
            <li><strong>Technical Cookies:</strong> Essential for the website to function. They handle traffic control, session identification, and secure navigation.</li>
            <li><strong>Personalization Cookies:</strong> These allow you to access the site with predefined features, such as your preferred language (English/Spanish).</li>
            <li><strong>Analytical Cookies:</strong> These help us quantify the number of visitors and perform statistical analysis on how users interact with our content to improve our services.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div id="third-party" class="content-section mb-5">
          <h3>3. Third-Party Services</h3>
          <p>This website uses trusted third-party services (such as Google Analytics or Google Maps) that may store cookies on your device to provide statistical data and interactive location services.</p>
          <div class="info-box" style="background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #0d6efd;">
            <i class="bi bi-info-circle" style="color: #0d6efd;"></i>
            <p style="margin: 0; display: inline-block; padding-left: 10px;">Some advanced tracking features may be temporarily limited during our 2026 platform update.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div id="control" class="content-section mb-5">
          <h3>4. How to manage or disable cookies</h3>
          <p>You can allow, block, or delete cookies at any time through your browser settings:</p>
          <div class="prohibited-list mt-3">
            <div class="prohibited-item mb-2 d-flex align-items-center">
              <i class="bi bi-browser-chrome me-2"></i>
              <span><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings > Privacy and security > Cookies and other site data.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="prohibited-item mb-2 d-flex align-items-center">
              <i class="bi bi-browser-safari me-2"></i>
              <span><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences > Privacy > Block all cookies.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="prohibited-item mb-2 d-flex align-items-center">
              <i class="bi bi-browser-edge me-2"></i>
              <span><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings > Cookies and site permissions.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section mb-5">
          <h3>5. Privacy and Consent</h3>
          <p>RumboMed does not store sensitive personal data through cookies. Any information collected (such as IP addresses for analytics) is handled according to our <a href="/en/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>. Your consent is requested upon your first visit to our site.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

